Package tictactoe.socket

Class GamingResponse

java.lang.Object
tictactoe.socket.Response
tictactoe.socket.GamingResponse
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class GamingResponse extends Response implements Serializable
Server response to a REQUEST_MOVE request. This class is a subclass of Response. It carries the opponent's last move and the active status of the game.

      public GamingResponse(ResponseStatus status, String message, Integer move, Boolean active)
      A constructor that sets all attributes of this class, including those inherited from Response. Calls the constructor of the superclass.
      Parameters:
      status - The status of the server response (SUCCESS or FAILURE).
      message - A string message description about the status of the client-server communication.
      move - An integer representing the last move made by the opponent (0-8).
      active - A boolean variable to indicate if the opponent is still active in the game.
